So the last week has been a bit of a rollercoaster to say the least.  The very short of it is that my dad had a medical issue which led him to the cardiologist last week.  That visit resulted in an intravenous examination of his heart last Friday, the results of which revealed multiple blockages (99%) and immediate admission to Palm Beach Gardens Medical Center.  At that point, the doctors weren’t sure how he hadn’t already dropped dead.  After multiple complications while being monitored around the clock in the hospital this week, he was able to have open-heart surgery on Wednesday.  The surgery went incredibly well, and he is now on the lengthy road to recovery!

I want to express my heartfelt gratitude to the surgeons, doctors, nurses, and staff at Palm Beach Gardens Medical Center.  They truly have been nothing short of amazing.  Also a huge thank you to all of our family and friends who took the time to visit, call, text, etc. and just be there for support for my mom, Sean, Jessica, Yosh, and me.  You all know who are, and we couldn’t be more grateful to have you in our lives.

If there’s a takeaway from this experience it is life is incredibly short and fragile.  Hug your loved ones and live life to the fullest…

@yoshuan @seanafeeney @jrhinelander @palmbeachgardensmedicalcenter
